               <head>Ilhamat-i Qudsi</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Gulistān by ʻAbd al-Karīm Qudsī Anṣārī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85129649" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_965-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>A series of edifying stories, some of mystical character, each introduced by the words سند است and ending with a moral in verse. The author appears to be ʻAbd al-Karīm Qudsī Anṣārī. Incomplete at end. 17th century.</p>
                        <p>The margins contain a numbers of different works:</p>
                        <p>ff. 1r-19r: a collection of verses existing of two short masnavis, a number of quatrains and single lines by an unamed author, possibly ʻAbd al-Karīm Anṣārī, 17th century;</p>
                        <p>ff. 27v-28v: the beginning of a commentary of the 
                <title key="work_21819">Gulistān</title>of 
                           <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_100206721" role="aut">Saʻdī</persName>by an unnamed author, 19th century;
                        </p>
                        <p>ff. 33v-48r: 
                <title key="work_21819">Tuḥfah-i Sulṭānīyah</title>(تحفهٔ سلطانیه) by 
                <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_23164717671502090603" role="aut">Ḥasan ibn Gul Muḥammad</persName>, an incomplete manual of the art of letter-writing with numerous specimens, 18th century.
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f8019" type="supplied">ʻAbd al-Karīm Qudsī Anṣārī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="person_f8019">عبد الکریم قدسی انصاری</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21819">Ilhāmāt-i Qudsī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_21819">الهامات قدسی</title>
                  </msItem>
